Review the full project package below for quality before it goes to the client.

Score each dimension 0-10 and decide whether to approve:
- consistency: do requirements, plan, tasks, and proposal agree with each other (no contradictions,
  no duplicated or orphaned tasks, dependencies make sense)?
- completeness: is every requirement and service covered by the plan, tasks, and proposal? Are any
  deliverables missing?
- clarity: is the proposal clear, well-structured, and client-ready?

APPROVAL POLICY — approve a solid, client-ready DRAFT, not a perfect document:
- Set approved=true when the package is coherent and client-ready overall (the kind of first
  draft a competent senior account manager would send), i.e. all three scores are >= 7 and there
  is no MATERIAL defect.
- Reject (approved=false) ONLY for a material defect:
  - a service the client explicitly requested is entirely missing from the plan/tasks/proposal,
  - a clear internal contradiction (e.g. a task references a milestone that doesn't exist),
  - empty, placeholder, or nonsensical content,
  - a genuinely critical requirement is absent and was not already clarified.
- Do NOT reject merely because you would like more detail, more specific dates, tighter budget
  breakdowns, or extra polish — those are acceptable in a proposal draft and are not defects.

When rejecting, set target_agent to the SINGLE agent whose output most needs the fix and put the
specific, actionable issue in feedback so that agent can address it.

